; Per PR-4 of #1262: the canonical form strips redundant unary
; `+` operators from numeric literals. `+0.1` and `0.1` parse to
; the same Decimal; the formatter emits one of them.
;
; This fixture documents the choice. The dispute is tracked in
; #1252 and (if reopened) any successor - preserving the user's
; lexical form would require extending the typed AST to carry a
; had-plus flag, which is a #1262 phase-5+ refactor.
2024-01-01 open Assets:Money
2024-07-20 * "leading plus sign on posting amount"
  Assets:Money +0.1 USD
  Expenses:Thingamabobs
